THREEjs

uses a right handed coordinate system
    - positive x moves right
    - positive y moves up
    - positive z moves towards the viewer, negative z moves away from the viewer 

front faces have a counter-clockwise winding order

GL.TriangleStrip and GL.TriangleFan aren't supported anymore (since version 112)


SHADERS

LYGIA Shader Library
https://lygia.xyz/
https://github.com/patriciogonzalezvivo/lygia/tree/main

https://github.com/stegu/webgl-noise
Noise lib for GLSL 1.20

https://thebookofshaders.com/11/

Generic 1,2,3 Noise shaders
https://gist.github.com/patriciogonzalezvivo/670c22f3966e662d2f83

20-something shaders: https://github.com/MasatoMakino/threejs-shader-materials
demo: https://masatomakino.github.io/threejs-shader-materials/demo/

Mesh replacement for THREE.Line Instead of using GL_LINE, it uses a strip of triangles billboarded.
https://github.com/spite/THREE.MeshLine

FXAA shader
https://github.com/mattdesl/three-shader-fxaa

Radial blur
https://github.com/ycw/three-radial-blur

Kawase blur
https://github.com/ycw/three-kawase-blur

Postprocessing collection
https://github.com/pmndrs/postprocessing